WEBVTT

00:00.130 --> 00:05.897
We've been talking a lot this weekend about the enjoyment of Jesus or enjoying Jesus.

00:05.997 --> 00:20.455
And I made the case on Friday that becoming a Christian or being born again or coming to saving faith is the awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

00:21.596 --> 00:29.426
And I pointed out that that is an unsettling fact for many because if you

00:31.554 --> 00:38.062
make them so closely related as to be necessarily in each other.

00:38.983 --> 00:41.066
If you're saved, you enjoy Jesus.

00:42.487 --> 00:45.892
To believe is to enjoy Jesus.

00:47.914 --> 00:55.804
It makes our faith feel fragile because our joy goes so up and down.

00:58.607 --> 01:01.010
So are you sure you want to do that, Piper?

01:01.858 --> 01:10.430
make them so closely connected, doesn't that tend to undermine people's assurance?

01:13.314 --> 01:21.685
And so let me head off at the past a misunderstanding, namely that Christian salvation is fragile.

01:22.406 --> 01:23.889
It's not.

01:23.909 --> 01:26.332
It's anything but fragile.

01:27.694 --> 01:30.738
Those whom he predestined, he called.

01:31.298 --> 01:34.162
And those of me called, he justified.

01:34.743 --> 01:38.089
And those of me justified, he glorified.

01:40.673 --> 01:42.215
That's as solid as it can get.

01:43.878 --> 01:47.724
From eternity to eternity, sure.

01:48.765 --> 01:51.890
An unbreakable chain from predestination

01:52.130 --> 02:02.482
to glorification and all the pieces in between of calling and justification and everything else that belongs to salvation is secure.

02:04.185 --> 02:09.090
If you're predestined, if you're called, if you're justified, you're going to make it.

02:10.152 --> 02:14.917
So I have no wobbly view of Christian salvation.

02:15.498 --> 02:22.066
I don't think it can be lost and therefore when I make it integral,

02:22.786 --> 02:30.734
to enjoying Jesus, I don't treat it as wobbly or uncertain.

02:32.415 --> 02:48.331
You don't solve the problem of the ups and downs of enjoying Jesus as if faith didn't have its ups and downs.

02:50.073 --> 02:51.314
It's like, oh,

02:51.778 --> 02:55.042
Joy is in emotion and therefore fragile.

02:55.422 --> 02:59.086
Faith is something that doesn't go up and down.

02:59.227 --> 02:59.947
That's not true.

03:01.709 --> 03:03.932
Jesus referred to little faith.

03:05.414 --> 03:09.138
Big, all your faith is great.

03:09.158 --> 03:12.362
Paul spoke of growing faith.

03:14.805 --> 03:19.570
So faith is not something that also does it.

03:20.610 --> 03:23.414
go up and down in our lives.

03:24.977 --> 03:31.767
So if the ups and downs of joy in our life feel threatening, then so will the ups and downs of faith.

03:31.928 --> 03:33.851
That's not the way to solve the problem.

03:36.074 --> 03:43.626
So we're going to talk about the ups and downs, especially the down of enjoying Jesus.

03:43.686 --> 03:48.914
That's where we're going this morning.

03:51.170 --> 03:59.659
I don't know what group I asked, I can't remember, but I love to ask groups, I'll ask you, what makes you think that you will wake up a believer tomorrow morning?

04:00.700 --> 04:06.347
What makes you think that you'll wake up and be a Christian in the morning?

04:08.429 --> 04:10.651
And there's a wrong answer to that question.

04:11.552 --> 04:18.760
And the wrong answer would be something like, I know beyond the shadow of it out that I will use my free will to believe in Jesus tomorrow morning.

04:19.000 --> 04:20.402
Well, you know no such thing.

04:24.770 --> 04:25.611
Here's what you know.

04:25.671 --> 04:31.300
Now on to him who is able to keep you from falling.

04:32.221 --> 04:44.801
And to present you blameless before the presence of his glory with rejoicing, to the only God I save you through Jesus Christ, our Lord be glory and authority and majesty and dominion forever.

04:44.861 --> 04:46.944
That's what you know.

04:46.964 --> 04:50.029
If you're a believer, he keeps his own.

04:51.191 --> 04:53.394
Those of me calls, he keeps.

04:53.506 --> 05:00.272
I will wake up a believer tomorrow morning because God has kept me or I won't be a believer tomorrow morning.

05:02.114 --> 05:05.337
We trust in God, not ourselves.

05:05.357 --> 05:15.447
So the security that we enjoy, the assurance that we have, that the ups and downs of our joy and the ups and downs of our faith don't destroy us.

05:15.507 --> 05:15.987
They won't.

05:16.508 --> 05:23.314
God has patterns built into the Bible to help us manage the downs.

05:23.810 --> 05:25.252
It's not hard to manage the ops.

05:26.673 --> 05:29.757
And that's what we're talking about this morning.

05:29.957 --> 05:34.662
There is a fight for faith.

05:35.763 --> 05:37.565
And the fight for faith is a fight for joy.

05:38.326 --> 05:48.978
If I was right on Friday night that to have saving faith in Jesus is to be awakened to the enjoyment of Jesus.

05:49.282 --> 05:55.009
So when Paul speaks to Timothy and says, fight the good fight of faith.

05:55.850 --> 05:58.133
It's the same as saying fight for joy.

05:59.074 --> 06:05.782
I wrote a book called When I Don't Desire God and the subtitle is How to Fight for Joy.

06:07.063 --> 06:09.326
I'm old and Paul was old.

06:09.827 --> 06:13.771
He called himself an old man one time in the book of Philemon and he was in prison.

06:14.292 --> 06:16.395
Great place to end your life by the way.

06:16.415 --> 06:19.218
It goes quicker that way probably.

06:22.146 --> 06:25.089
in case you're wondering what to do with your last 20 years.

06:28.833 --> 06:39.504
He was in prison, and he wrote the last book of the New Testament that he wrote, 2 Timothy, and he said, I have fought the good fight.

06:40.105 --> 06:41.486
I have finished the course.

06:42.307 --> 06:48.754
I have kept the faith, which I take to mean old men fight to the end, and they better not stop.

06:50.306 --> 06:56.572
If you think that you can fight for 60 or 80 years and then stop for a year or two, you're crazy.

06:57.973 --> 06:59.655
The devil does not sleep.

07:01.476 --> 07:05.680
His fiery darts shoot at old people and young people.

07:06.521 --> 07:09.424
We fight to the end and God has taught us how to do it.

07:09.764 --> 07:10.845
And that's what we're talking about.

07:11.766 --> 07:20.114
How to fight your way through the slump when you wake up and there's almost no joy.

07:21.730 --> 07:22.211
in Jesus.

07:25.054 --> 07:30.762
So if you have a Bible, if you hope you do, at least on your phone, let's go to, oh, you just turned your phones off.

07:30.782 --> 07:34.267
How do you do?

07:34.287 --> 07:35.709
Got print Bibles around here.

07:35.769 --> 07:36.650
That's good.

07:37.391 --> 07:39.714
Let's go to the Bible.

07:41.016 --> 07:41.857
However you've got it.

07:42.738 --> 07:43.479
Psalm 40.

07:43.519 --> 07:48.946
And we're going to read verses one to three.

07:50.434 --> 08:07.654
which are a pattern of how David managed his loss of spiritual dynamic joy.

08:09.076 --> 08:09.817
What did he do?

08:11.319 --> 08:17.426
And I think as Christians on this side of the cross, we can

08:18.114 --> 08:20.437
embrace these verses as our own.

08:25.043 --> 08:47.794
Paul said in Galatians 4, when the fullness of time had come, God sent forth His Son, born of woman, born under the law, that He might redeem those who were under the law, in order that they might be adopted as sons.

08:48.738 --> 09:02.395
We know God today as our Father in a unique and special way unknown in the same detail in the Old Testament.

09:02.415 --> 09:04.738
They didn't know how this was going to work.

09:04.758 --> 09:17.074
They didn't know that blood was going to be shed by the incarnate God as the Messiah who would cover all the sins old and New Testament and who would bring the saints into a sweet intimate

09:17.602 --> 09:30.419
child-adopted relationship with the Father so that when we call upon God like this text does, we're calling now upon God as a father that we have because of adoption through the blood of Jesus.

09:30.799 --> 09:34.804
So I'm reading this text because I read my whole Bible.

09:36.807 --> 09:39.250
I understand it as a completed

09:39.490 --> 09:43.914
hold the Old Testament preparing and the New Testament fulfilling.

09:44.355 --> 09:53.223
And I think you then did stand back and see all the promises of God bought by Jesus Christ and you can make the Old Testament your book.

09:53.723 --> 10:00.630
And so I'm reading this as my Christian book here, these three verses in Psalm 40.

10:01.771 --> 10:04.013
I think Jesus bought this text for you.

10:05.514 --> 10:06.996
If you are in Him, it's yours.

10:08.277 --> 10:09.458
To the choir master.

10:10.274 --> 10:15.901
a psalm of David, I waited patiently for the Lord.

10:17.623 --> 10:19.806
He inclined to me and heard my cry.

10:21.287 --> 10:32.481
He drew me up from the pit of destruction out of the myry bog and set my feet upon a rock, making my steps secure.

10:33.282 --> 10:40.050
He put a new song in my mouth, a song of praise to our God, many

10:40.354 --> 10:46.002
will see and fear and put their trust in the Lord.

10:47.383 --> 10:51.349
Now I think that's a pattern of life that we live.

10:52.670 --> 10:57.617
I'm tempted to say every day, at least regularly.

10:58.999 --> 11:07.410
So I'm, I'm asking, is it, is it normal to have Christian seasons in the pit with the king?

11:09.090 --> 11:10.853
And what do you do when you go there?

11:11.293 --> 11:13.256
That's what this message is about.

11:13.296 --> 11:16.020
And that's what this text, I think, answers.

11:16.761 --> 11:18.163
I see six stages.

11:18.724 --> 11:22.650
If I were teaching a class instead of preaching a sermon, I would have you find the stages.

11:24.493 --> 11:28.258
First, David is in a muddy pit, verse two.

11:29.160 --> 11:32.625
Calls it a pit of destruction, Mirey Bog in the ESV.

11:33.346 --> 11:38.173
Second, he cries out to God from this pit for help.

11:38.193 --> 11:38.994
Verse one,

11:39.266 --> 11:40.127
He heard my cry.

11:41.369 --> 11:43.272
Three, he waits.

11:43.793 --> 11:44.254
How long?

11:44.434 --> 11:45.215
I don't know how long.

11:45.296 --> 11:46.678
I'm glad he didn't tell me how long.

11:47.319 --> 11:49.803
He waits for the Lord.

11:50.404 --> 11:53.929
Verse one, I waited patiently for the Lord.

11:54.811 --> 11:59.879
Four, God draws him up out of the pit into safety.

11:59.979 --> 12:03.625
Verse two, he drew me up out of the pit.

12:03.645 --> 12:06.930
Five, God gives David a new song.

12:07.714 --> 12:11.680
to sing, probably the one we're reading, Psalm 40.

12:12.421 --> 12:14.965
Verse three, he put a new song in my mouth.

12:16.026 --> 12:20.813
And finally verse, or step six, many see.

12:21.675 --> 12:29.606
Many others see what happened to David and they fear and they put their trust in the Lord.

12:29.807 --> 12:32.050
Verse three, many will see in fear.

12:32.162 --> 12:33.464
and put their trust in the Lord.

12:33.484 --> 12:46.661
So I'll give them names and then we'll take them one at a time and walk you through them because this is where we, I want you to simply take away from this message, okay, that's what I'll do.

12:47.022 --> 12:47.643
That's what I'll do.

12:48.864 --> 12:55.093
When my spirits are low and when my joy seems to vanish, this is what I'm going to do.

12:55.593 --> 12:59.218
So I want you to just get a real clear sense of what these six stages are.

13:01.081 --> 13:02.002
The king's pit.

13:02.754 --> 13:13.388
The kings cry, the kings patience, the kings rescue, the kings song, and the kings influence.

13:14.490 --> 13:17.414
And I think you can just put your name on it if you're a Christian.

13:17.634 --> 13:22.580
You just put your name on it and say that was the saints experience in the Old Testament.

13:23.121 --> 13:24.984
I'm in the Messiah, Jesus Christ.

13:25.625 --> 13:28.008
That can be my experience today.

13:28.228 --> 13:29.570
So let's take them one at a time.

13:29.870 --> 13:32.754
First, he's in the pits.

13:34.114 --> 13:35.216
What was that?

13:35.316 --> 13:35.857
What is that?

13:36.377 --> 13:37.199
There's a little pit.

13:37.239 --> 13:39.081
Is that a picture of something?

13:40.624 --> 13:42.787
In ESV, it's the pit of destruction.

13:43.308 --> 13:45.691
In the King James, it's a horrible pit.

13:46.072 --> 13:47.954
In the RSV, it's a desolate pit.

13:48.415 --> 13:51.420
In the NIV, it's a slimy pit.

13:52.341 --> 13:55.746
You look up the word and get the most root definition.

13:56.147 --> 14:01.234
It has to do with roaring and a tumel, which is an odd picture for a pit.

14:02.050 --> 14:05.095
You don't think of, I'm in a pit and there's a storm in the pit.

14:05.295 --> 14:05.976
That's odd.

14:06.557 --> 14:08.781
These are not photographs, right?

14:08.801 --> 14:16.734
These are word pictures chosen to help us feel the soul condition that he was in.

14:16.754 --> 14:19.238
And then you got mud, mire.

14:20.620 --> 14:21.842
And they don't seem to go together.

14:22.403 --> 14:29.234
This roaring pit, like a well, like 30, 40 feet down,

14:29.794 --> 14:36.001
And you're down there, and there's a storm down there, and there's mud down there.

14:36.042 --> 14:37.643
It's Meyer.

14:38.745 --> 14:49.057
It reminded me of, because I'm reading, I suppose, through Jeremiah right now in my devotions, what happened to Jeremiah when Zedekiah got so ticked at this prophet.

14:49.658 --> 14:51.660
Here's what it says in Jeremiah 38.6.

14:51.720 --> 14:59.730
So they took Jeremiah and cast him into the cistern of Malchia, the king's son,

15:00.386 --> 15:03.709
which was in the court of the guard letting Jeremiah down with ropes.

15:03.890 --> 15:05.131
That was nice at least.

15:05.952 --> 15:14.100
And there was no water in the cistern, but only Meyer and Jeremiah sank in the Meyer.

15:15.141 --> 15:15.842
That's scary.

15:17.764 --> 15:19.025
Quicksand is scary.

15:19.145 --> 15:21.047
I don't like movies that have quicksand.

15:21.788 --> 15:23.570
There's horrible, I mean nightmares.

15:24.651 --> 15:27.954
They can't stand the thought of thinking in Quicksand.

15:28.130 --> 15:31.735
And that seems to be something of the picture here.

15:31.856 --> 15:33.919
It's helplessness, it's desperation.

15:35.080 --> 15:37.023
Air starts to become precious to you.

15:37.063 --> 15:38.766
Am I ever going to get out of here?

15:38.806 --> 15:45.315
That's a description of the emotion of your life at times, maybe today.

15:46.477 --> 15:47.399
Eventually it will be.

15:51.224 --> 15:57.874
Helpless, desperate, maybe hopeless, because you just can't feel anything anymore.

15:59.266 --> 16:10.100
A breaking point for an overworked businessman, exasperation to the limit of a mom with three kids that are all crying and they're little and she's just at her wits end.

16:10.140 --> 16:13.004
Too many classes for a student.

16:13.064 --> 16:14.205
I can't do this, Dad.

16:14.265 --> 16:16.748
I can't do this, this college thing.

16:16.768 --> 16:19.872
A powerful enemy coming against you.

16:19.892 --> 16:23.757
Some grinding stress of a long illness.

16:23.998 --> 16:25.640
I mean, pick your desperation.

16:26.521 --> 16:27.442
Life is hard.

16:29.058 --> 16:29.839
And God is good.

16:30.941 --> 16:32.283
We like to sing that, don't we?

16:35.789 --> 16:37.111
So that's the pit.

16:38.313 --> 16:40.737
We don't know what it was for David.

16:41.478 --> 16:49.391
And I'm glad we don't know, because I think that invites you in to say yours too.

16:52.977 --> 16:56.402
The king's pit, and then the king's cry, number two.

16:56.546 --> 16:59.369
Verse 1, I waited patiently for the Lord.

16:59.689 --> 17:03.494
He inclined to me and heard my cry.

17:03.894 --> 17:10.962
I think one of the reasons God calls David a man after his own heart while he has such an affection for David is because he cried so much.

17:11.903 --> 17:14.526
He cried out so much.

17:14.886 --> 17:18.170
Here's Psalm 6, I am weary with my mourning.

17:18.210 --> 17:22.274
Every night I flood my bed with tears.

17:23.496 --> 17:25.458
I drench my couch

17:25.538 --> 17:27.380
with my weeping.

17:29.543 --> 17:33.449
That's the man after God's own heart.

17:33.469 --> 17:37.034
Psalm 56, put my tears in your bottle.

17:38.235 --> 17:41.520
Are they not in your book?

17:41.540 --> 17:45.685
And of course, Jesus, blessed are those who mourn.

17:46.887 --> 17:55.058
It is a beautiful thing when a broken man genuinely cries out to God.

17:56.482 --> 18:10.738
It is not a beautiful thing when a macho jock tries to make his way to shore after getting a cramp hiding the fact that he's about to die and he's not going to let anybody know about it.

18:11.760 --> 18:12.641
That's not beautiful.

18:13.321 --> 18:14.322
He thinks it's beautiful.

18:14.463 --> 18:16.365
It's not beautiful, not to God.

18:18.908 --> 18:22.252
I remember when I was in Daytona Beach on vacation with my parents.

18:22.392 --> 18:24.434
It's a little six-year-old or so.

18:25.410 --> 18:29.596
and you wait out just a little too far, and you know how the current works.

18:29.656 --> 18:38.950
It can just, and little kids just totally not ready for the power of the undertow sweeps me off my feet, and my first words are, Daddy?

18:38.990 --> 18:42.635
That's what God wants to hear.

18:43.697 --> 18:44.979
That's what God wants to hear.

18:45.039 --> 18:49.866
None of this fake, I don't need any help.

18:49.886 --> 18:50.747
That's ridiculous.

18:52.690 --> 18:55.314
You better own the need for help.

18:55.938 --> 19:01.486
women and men and little children and teenagers, we need help.

19:02.067 --> 19:07.474
And so he cries out and God is very pleased with the cry of his people.

19:10.518 --> 19:15.606
Blessed is the man, this is verse four, the next verse.

19:16.467 --> 19:24.498
Blessed is the man who has made the Lord his trust and who has not turned to the proud.

19:25.410 --> 19:29.816
In other words, when you cry out, be sure to cry out to God.

19:31.157 --> 19:37.185
That's a lot of people who are willing to recognize the need for help and they don't ask God.

19:37.205 --> 19:38.186
They ask other people.

19:39.548 --> 19:45.696
God, he's kind of maybe a last resort, not a first resort.

19:45.716 --> 19:46.657
That's backwards.

19:47.278 --> 19:48.359
That's his backwards.

19:49.461 --> 19:51.703
God should be our first resort.

19:51.723 --> 19:53.746
Do you remember Ace of the King?

19:55.170 --> 20:02.737
Oh man, every time I read the stories of these kings and the old stuff, I just shake my head and say, oh my goodness, won't they ever learn?

20:02.777 --> 20:10.004
And of course, won't Piper ever learn to trust the Lord and not be anxious?

20:10.065 --> 20:23.858
But Asa relied upon Syria instead of the Lord and God spanked him for it, didn't kill him, just spanked him and disciplined him, and then

20:24.034 --> 20:25.556
You think, okay, he's got it.

20:26.417 --> 20:29.120
And at the end of his life, this is second chronicle, 1612.

20:29.320 --> 20:38.650
In the 39th year of his reign, Asa was diseased in his feet, and his disease became severe.

20:39.451 --> 20:48.180
And even in his disease, he did not seek the Lord, but he sought help from physicians.

20:50.103 --> 20:53.266
No, I thank God for physicians.

20:54.178 --> 20:56.000
This is not anti-physician.

20:56.400 --> 20:59.223
This is anti-making physicians or God.

21:01.566 --> 21:05.130
This is anti-defaulting to physicians.

21:05.671 --> 21:07.493
Oh yes, later God.

21:08.594 --> 21:10.195
That's what this text is against.

21:11.817 --> 21:16.182
When David was in the pit, he cried out to the Lord.

21:19.025 --> 21:23.570
And the Lord uses all kinds of means and medicine is a great

21:23.874 --> 21:29.022
gift of common grace that we should all be very, very thankful for.

21:29.042 --> 21:32.007
It is better to take refuge.

21:32.027 --> 21:32.988
This is Psalm 118.

21:33.329 --> 21:36.934
It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in man.

21:38.256 --> 21:42.863
It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in princes.

21:43.504 --> 21:49.073
So when you're in the pit, you cry out to God.

21:49.994 --> 21:52.498
Now he may use a therapist.

21:52.642 --> 21:57.969
A Christian counselor, may use a pastor, may use the Bible.

21:59.110 --> 22:05.158
He has a hundred ways to meet you and rescue you, but you call out to him.

22:05.218 --> 22:06.940
That's number two.

22:07.701 --> 22:14.850
The king's pit, the king's cry, and now thirdly, the king's patient waiting, the king's patience.

22:17.653 --> 22:21.298
Verse one, I waited patiently.

22:22.050 --> 22:22.911
for the Lord.

22:22.931 --> 22:35.629
The reason that's so important for us to hear is because waiting, I think Marshall's breakout yesterday was on waiting.

22:36.430 --> 22:41.537
Waiting is a huge portion of the Christian life.

22:43.260 --> 22:50.610
We could wish that answers came as soon as the request was made and they don't

22:51.426 --> 22:52.808
They don't come that way usually.

22:54.149 --> 22:56.171
God's timing is rarely your timing.

22:57.253 --> 23:00.877
I was a pastor for 33 years and we were always desperate for something.

23:01.938 --> 23:02.959
Something wasn't working.

23:03.780 --> 23:07.504
Come to the end of the year, you need a third of your budget in December.

23:07.524 --> 23:08.185
Very typical.

23:08.345 --> 23:10.408
Like, oh my goodness.

23:10.448 --> 23:12.470
Four weeks left, need a million dollars.

23:15.393 --> 23:19.378
And God cancels your first service with a snowstorm.

23:20.354 --> 23:20.975
like Gideon.

23:21.015 --> 23:24.501
You got too many Sundays to get a million dollars.

23:24.521 --> 23:25.783
Going to take one of them away.

23:25.823 --> 23:27.466
Nobody's showing up today.

23:29.189 --> 23:31.532
That's just the way it worked over and over again.

23:31.552 --> 23:33.095
And he came through.

23:33.115 --> 23:34.557
He came through.

23:35.138 --> 23:39.225
My God will supply all your needs according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.

23:39.245 --> 23:40.487
If you don't get it, you don't need it.

23:42.430 --> 23:45.796
That's why I told the elders, if we don't get it, we don't need it.

23:45.816 --> 23:47.058
That's what it says in the Bible.

23:49.506 --> 23:51.649
He will supply every need.

23:54.794 --> 23:57.077
And our timing is seldom his.

23:58.379 --> 24:05.470
He knows the time for joy and truly will send it when he sees it meet.

24:06.692 --> 24:16.306
When he has tried and purge thee do thee and finds thee free from all deceit, he comes to thee all unaware.

24:16.802 --> 24:19.867
and makes thee own his loving care."

24:19.887 --> 24:20.648
I love that song.

24:21.209 --> 24:23.152
It's called, If Thou But Suffered God to Guide Thee.

24:23.192 --> 24:24.815
I learned it in Germany, in German.

24:25.957 --> 24:37.035
And now I've got seven verses, and that one right there, a timing of God is simply sovereignly wise and seldom your timing.

24:37.976 --> 24:39.078
God knows what he's doing.

24:39.138 --> 24:39.579
We wait.

24:39.939 --> 24:44.146
Waiting is a huge part of the Christian life.

24:45.506 --> 24:47.569
Evil doers will be cut off.

24:47.629 --> 24:55.481
This is Psalm 37, but those who wait for the Lord, they will inherit the land.

24:56.542 --> 25:11.584
A great part of waiting is meekness and humility because a verse, two verses later it says, the humble will inherit the land and will delight themselves in abundance.

25:11.865 --> 25:12.786
So the

25:13.154 --> 25:15.878
Waiters, those who wait will inherit the land.

25:16.018 --> 25:18.662
And then it says the humble will inherit the land.

25:19.823 --> 25:22.547
To wait, you've got to be humble.

25:25.511 --> 25:30.738
So you're sitting in a doctor's office and he had an emergency.

25:31.800 --> 25:32.581
And he's not there.

25:34.043 --> 25:35.505
And the appointments are backing up.

25:36.606 --> 25:42.194
And this room is full of upset people.

25:43.650 --> 25:51.623
Now, who are the people who are making themselves a perfect pain in their rear for these poor receptionists?

25:51.643 --> 25:54.347
Proud people, not humble people.

25:55.008 --> 26:01.118
People who presume upon their rights, the humble people understand reality.

26:02.340 --> 26:04.463
Nobody's planned anything against you here.

26:05.205 --> 26:06.807
Somebody's dying somewhere.

26:08.069 --> 26:08.530
Cool it.

26:12.834 --> 26:17.399
to wait as we ought to wait requires humility.

26:17.880 --> 26:19.542
It also requires hope.

26:21.184 --> 26:25.649
Psalm 39, and now Lord, what do I wait for?

26:25.950 --> 26:29.614
My hope is in you, or Psalm 130.

26:29.914 --> 26:34.940
I wait for the Lord, my soul waits, and in his word do I hope.

26:36.923 --> 26:39.826
Waiting is not listlessness.

26:43.202 --> 26:44.684
That's not the posture.

26:45.746 --> 26:54.098
As a deer, plants, as a deer, pants for the water brooks, so my soul pants for thee, oh God, my soul thirsts for God.

26:54.118 --> 27:00.468
There's a leaning in to when will he arrive and what will he do and how will he bring me out of this?

27:00.508 --> 27:03.412
He's coming, I know he's coming, he's gonna come at the right time.

27:03.672 --> 27:12.946
He's gonna bring the right deliverance and I'm waiting humbly because I don't deserve anything better than this and I'm waiting hopefully because he's a good father.

27:13.922 --> 27:16.625
That's the posture of waiting.

27:18.086 --> 27:26.354
The king's pit, the king's cry, the king's patience, and now the king's rescue, verse two.

27:27.295 --> 27:38.706
He drew me up from the pit of destruction out of the myry bog and set my feet upon a rock, making my steps secure.

27:40.007 --> 27:43.250
There's a world of difference between quicksand and rock.

27:44.962 --> 27:46.203
It's a beautiful picture.

27:46.564 --> 27:55.012
You drew me up by this slime in which I was sinking and sinking and sinking and he picks me up and puts me on a rock solid.

27:56.473 --> 27:58.615
That we weren't as Christians.

27:58.896 --> 28:01.058
We weren't saying God's not real.

28:01.498 --> 28:08.665
We were just admitting my emotions are not fully in sync with the realities I know exist.

28:08.945 --> 28:11.368
I feel like I'm sinking.

28:12.909 --> 28:13.810
That's reality.

28:16.610 --> 28:21.315
And he comes and he was secure in his hand all along.

28:22.977 --> 28:24.759
And now he makes you feel it, right?

28:25.180 --> 28:30.125
What a difference to be sinking and then to be standing on a rock.

28:30.205 --> 28:31.447
That's what changes.

28:31.987 --> 28:38.635
He ministers to your soul so deeply that you feel like you're on a rock.

28:38.835 --> 28:42.939
And I don't know what the rescue was from.

28:43.000 --> 28:45.202
Could have been disease.

28:45.890 --> 28:48.312
Maybe he was very sick and about to die.

28:48.853 --> 28:53.918
Psalm 30, oh Lord my God, I cried to you for help and you have healed me.

28:55.619 --> 28:56.440
That's sickness.

28:56.720 --> 28:57.801
That's one way of rescue.

28:58.302 --> 29:00.124
Or it may have been from enemies.

29:00.504 --> 29:09.493
Psalm 69, save me, oh God, more in number than the hairs in my head are those who want to destroy me.

29:11.174 --> 29:15.058
Or it might have been guilt, very aware of that psalm.

29:15.138 --> 29:22.349
Right, so 51, be gracious to me, oh God, wash me thoroughly from my iniquity, cleanse me from my sin.

29:22.409 --> 29:30.020
So I'm glad again, it doesn't say not only how long he waited, it doesn't say what he got rescued from.

29:30.080 --> 29:45.042
God is so merciful, he will rescue you from anything, anything if you will call to him like a little child and trust him to come

29:46.178 --> 29:55.352
So the king's pit, the king's cry, the king's patience, the king's rescue, and now the king's song.

29:58.136 --> 30:06.468
Verse three, he put a new song in my mouth, a song of praise to our God.

30:07.911 --> 30:09.773
What is singing signify?

30:11.135 --> 30:15.602
If your heart is singing and your mouth is singing, you have

30:17.058 --> 30:19.261
felt something is very precious.

30:20.483 --> 30:27.132
You are so thankful for something that words are not quite adequate.

30:27.573 --> 30:28.835
They have to be sung.

30:28.855 --> 30:31.178
A poem has to be written.

30:31.198 --> 30:38.729
A song has to be sung because my heart has been made so glad ordinary language is not adequate anymore.

30:39.250 --> 30:41.012
That's what singing says.

30:41.793 --> 30:44.978
Something is so good, so precious.

30:46.018 --> 30:52.127
All of us gravitate towards dullness, no songs.

30:53.329 --> 30:55.532
Most people don't sing through the day.

30:55.712 --> 30:56.694
It's an unusual person.

30:57.936 --> 31:06.889
Johnny Eric Santada, I said Saturday night that she's one of my heroes, and that's what marks her life in her paralysis.

31:07.450 --> 31:08.091
She sings.

31:09.373 --> 31:11.876
Anytime I'm with her, she starts a song.

31:11.896 --> 31:12.978
You know this song, John?

31:15.874 --> 31:18.817
She knows every hymn there exists.

31:20.058 --> 31:21.619
It seems like, from memory.

31:23.381 --> 31:24.983
Because she's a thankful person.

31:25.023 --> 31:28.986
She has cultivated deeply, deeply thankful heart.

31:29.927 --> 31:30.788
She knows the pits.

31:32.349 --> 31:38.615
You can't be paralyzed from age 17 to 76, or birthday was day before yesterday.

31:39.837 --> 31:42.439
You can't be paralyzed for that long and not have pits.

31:43.780 --> 31:45.682
But oh, how she

31:45.922 --> 31:49.927
has grown to be thankful and therefore sing.

31:50.067 --> 32:08.211
So if you were God, and you look down and you saw your people songless, and their hearts were not ecstatic over the relationship that you have given them forever, what would you do?

32:09.453 --> 32:13.618
Well, one of the things he does is to put you in the pit.

32:15.298 --> 32:24.392
and stripped from you many blessings for a season so that when you come up, you sing.

32:24.473 --> 32:26.195
That's what it says.

32:26.235 --> 32:28.980
He put a new song in my mouth.

32:29.000 --> 32:30.222
Why did he sing a new song?

32:30.242 --> 32:31.303
Because he was in the pit.

32:32.826 --> 32:33.747
That's how it works.

32:35.210 --> 32:36.572
So I'm 14 years old.

32:38.034 --> 32:38.895
I love to swim.

32:40.318 --> 32:43.122
I love to swim underwater, not on top of water.

32:45.218 --> 32:48.201
There was a pool in their neighborhood that was 40 feet long and 20 feet wide.

32:49.803 --> 32:52.506
And I loved to see how many laps I could do underwater.

32:53.527 --> 32:56.210
One, two, three, four.

32:58.092 --> 33:00.695
I loved to just, you know, stay underwater as long as I could.

33:00.715 --> 33:01.876
I thought that was cool.

33:05.600 --> 33:07.162
At the deep end, it's nine feet deep.

33:08.443 --> 33:12.968
And there's a grade at the bottom that covers the drainage.

33:12.988 --> 33:15.090
And my job was

33:15.298 --> 33:18.461
Clean the great.

33:18.481 --> 33:21.164
And one day, my finger got stuck in the great.

33:25.529 --> 33:29.313
And air became very precious.

33:31.135 --> 33:33.237
You got 30 seconds.

33:33.257 --> 33:35.420
You can chew your finger off, maybe.

33:37.161 --> 33:37.842
Or you can drown.

33:39.144 --> 33:42.247
Or you can cry out to the Lord, which I did.

33:43.408 --> 33:45.170
I didn't wait patiently.

33:45.314 --> 33:46.855
Skip that step.

33:50.679 --> 33:55.504
And he let me loose and set my feet up on a concrete deck.

33:58.947 --> 34:01.509
And I loved air.

34:03.551 --> 34:06.394
If you'd asked me an hour earlier, you love air?

34:06.434 --> 34:09.677
You singing songs to air?

34:09.737 --> 34:11.599
I'd look at you funny.

34:13.280 --> 34:15.282
Now I'm singing songs to air.

34:16.002 --> 34:17.284
That's what he does.

34:19.488 --> 34:23.995
If you've got a better way for him to do it, then you can counsel him about that.

34:26.018 --> 34:34.732
But the Bible says nobody has counseled the Lord, so skip that step and just admit that he's wise and he loves you.

34:35.634 --> 34:40.722
He wants you to love him like I loved air, precious air, sweet

34:41.666 --> 34:46.351
air, inestimable air, give a million dollars for every breath of air.

34:46.411 --> 34:49.293
That's how important and precious God is.

34:50.895 --> 34:56.921
And if he has to lay us low in order to bring us up to give us a new song, he'll do it.

34:57.521 --> 34:58.803
He wants you to sing a new song.

34:58.823 --> 35:08.392
And so if you loved him that way, if your enjoyment of Jesus were that constant, then you might not have to endure as many down seasons.

35:09.893 --> 35:10.674
So that's

35:11.298 --> 35:12.740
Number five.

35:14.422 --> 35:19.269
Maybe before I turn to number six, I see a reminder here.

35:19.649 --> 35:24.336
I wrote down yesterday a new song.

35:24.396 --> 35:26.178
He says, put a new song in my mouth.

35:28.441 --> 35:30.644
Or maybe an old song sung in a new way.

35:31.165 --> 35:37.474
But I do think it would be good to say to you as a church, go ahead and sing a new song.

35:38.095 --> 35:38.775
Clearly you do.

35:38.816 --> 35:40.658
I don't know any of these songs that you say.

35:42.114 --> 35:43.777
I mean, I recognize them sort of.

35:47.623 --> 35:48.764
They're all made new, right?

35:49.666 --> 35:52.550
That's got a biblical, there's a biblical warrant for that.

35:52.570 --> 35:55.195
If you wondered, why do they do that here?

35:56.256 --> 35:57.678
Sing a new song to the Lord.

35:58.780 --> 36:01.565
So old songs become new, new songs are new.

36:02.807 --> 36:10.098
And old songs, the reason I pause here on music is because I think it's true that

36:11.330 --> 36:18.878
Most rich, deep, beautiful songs historically have come out of the pit.

36:20.439 --> 36:25.464
You walk through a pit, you come up out and a new song is given to you.

36:25.845 --> 36:28.828
And you write it down and they sing it for 500 years.

36:30.670 --> 36:38.738
So the old song says, when peace like a river, a tendeth my way,

36:39.394 --> 36:41.857
when sorrows like sea billows roll.

36:42.898 --> 36:51.309
The new song says, Blessed be your name in the land that is plentiful or the streams of abundance flow.

36:51.369 --> 36:55.715
Blessed be your name when I'm found in the desert place.

36:56.976 --> 37:04.786
Though I walk through the wilderness, billows, desert, pit, that's where songs come from.

37:07.074 --> 37:11.060
If you'd ever walk through any pit, you probably will sing light songs.

37:12.042 --> 37:21.055
They won't ever have the feel of blood, pain, suffering, sustaining faithful grace from God.

37:21.616 --> 37:25.422
But you walk through pits and then you come out, he puts a new song in your mouth.

37:25.722 --> 37:30.930
That song is going to have a flavor that makes it go deep with people and lasts for a long time.

37:32.674 --> 37:34.676
Number six, the king's influence.

37:34.777 --> 37:35.798
This is so remarkable.

37:36.078 --> 37:36.839
We end with this.

37:37.460 --> 37:42.946
And the surprising thing, and I suppose it's what made me love this unit.

37:43.647 --> 37:46.110
I preached on this one other time, 1980.

37:46.351 --> 37:49.154
I was a brand new pastor, 34.

37:49.514 --> 37:53.239
We were doing a summer songs we called them, and I did this.

37:53.319 --> 37:56.323
I called it In the Pits with the King back in those days.

37:57.024 --> 38:02.290
And I loved this song,

38:02.466 --> 38:06.232
this unit because it ends on evangelism.

38:09.177 --> 38:10.580
Many will see in fear.

38:10.660 --> 38:11.441
This is verse three.

38:12.142 --> 38:16.770
Many will see in fear and put their trust in the Lord.

38:20.336 --> 38:21.558
You just want to laugh, don't you?

38:21.578 --> 38:23.882
Like, oh, the whole thing was about evangelism.

38:26.246 --> 38:27.628
You want to win people to Jesus?

38:27.969 --> 38:28.690
Get in a bit.

38:29.218 --> 38:32.924
I mean, let him put you in a pit and don't get angry at him.

38:33.565 --> 38:35.508
Many will see and fear.

38:35.568 --> 38:40.435
Now, what do they see and what do they fear and then trust?

38:41.437 --> 38:43.019
That's an interesting way to say it, right?

38:43.039 --> 38:45.303
They see, they fear, they trust.

38:47.647 --> 38:57.682
Well, what they see is a Christian who in humility and patience endures a hard thing.

38:58.722 --> 39:01.045
Pick your hard thing, a very hard thing.

39:01.205 --> 39:05.451
They're watching you, and you endure it.

39:05.511 --> 39:16.104
You wait patiently, you are humble, and you are trusting, and you're calling out to God for help and for deliverance.

39:17.065 --> 39:27.218
And after a season, God comes through for you and re-establishes your hope and your strength, and maybe even puts your feet upon a healed

39:27.394 --> 39:29.736
rock a delivered rock.

39:30.737 --> 39:42.530
So they're watching this and they see your unusual counter-intuitive enduring a hardship as you trust and call out to God.

39:44.031 --> 39:54.642
And then they see God's faithfulness and he comes through and then they think, well, if that's real, I'm in trouble.

39:56.866 --> 39:57.427
That's the fear.

39:57.647 --> 40:09.125
If that's real, if that kind of faith is real and that kind of God is real, then I don't have it and I'm afraid.

40:10.847 --> 40:16.856
And then God gives them what they need and they trust in the Lord.

40:16.916 --> 40:17.938
It's a beautiful

40:18.498 --> 40:21.382
It's a beautiful thing to believe, and that certainly is the case.

40:21.482 --> 40:27.869
I mean, every suffering person I know who has responded like this is a strengthening to my faith.

40:29.471 --> 40:31.314
I've got my heroes.

40:31.414 --> 40:39.043
Heroism to me is enduring much hardship for great causes.

40:40.965 --> 40:47.954
So anybody can be a hero if they endure hardship

40:48.514 --> 40:52.220
for a great purpose in reliance upon the Lord.

40:52.341 --> 40:58.251
So it strengthens new believers by bringing them and it strengthens old believers.

40:59.092 --> 41:05.062
So what a surprise the whole story turns out to be a story of personal evangelism.

41:06.104 --> 41:07.787
So how shall we win others to Christ?

41:07.867 --> 41:08.588
I'll end with this.

41:10.291 --> 41:14.418
When you are in the pits with the king, which you will be,

41:16.098 --> 41:20.965
cry out to the Lord like a helpless child, not a self-sufficient person.

41:23.568 --> 41:26.933
Then humbly and hopefully wait patiently for the Lord.

41:27.554 --> 41:30.217
His timing will be your timing, it'll be perfect.

41:32.621 --> 41:45.458
When He comes in His own time and makes you secure, then sing a new song to the Lord and sing it out loud and sing it in public

41:46.210 --> 41:52.600
And God may be pleased to cause many to see and fear and put their trust in the Lord.

41:54.062 --> 42:13.874
So Father, I ask that that would be the wonder that we would all experience here at this church, our church, that we would be granted the grace to endure your disciplinary pits, that we would be patient, that we would call upon you,

42:14.530 --> 42:15.531
and that you would show up.

42:15.551 --> 42:37.415
I pray that you'd show up this morning for people who came in here with their feet sinking in the mire and that they would be given a rock, that they would walk out of here stable, secure, confident that you care and you have come through for them.

42:38.336 --> 42:44.242
They many, many in Midlothian and all this region see and fear

42:45.122 --> 42:46.450
and put their trust in the Lord.

